        Route to Service





        Current Flow (Without Rate Limiting)

        Right now your gateway works like this:

        Client
           │
           ▼
        API Gateway
           │
           ▼
        JwtGlobalFilter
           │
           ▼
        Validate JWT
           │
           ▼
        Forward Request
           │
           ▼
        Action Service / Query Service

        Suppose a malicious user sends 10,000 requests per second.

        Your gateway will:

        Read the Authorization header
        Parse the JWT
        Verify the signature
        Extract claims
        Add X-USER
        Add X-ROLES
        Forward the request

        All 10,000 times.

        That wastes CPU before you've even decided whether the request should be allowed.

        Production Flow

        Instead, production systems do this:

        Client
           │
           ▼
        RateLimitFilter

        The very first question becomes:

        "Should I even allow this request?"

        If the answer is No, the request is rejected immediately.

        The JWT is never parsed.

        The microservice is never called.

        The database is never touched.

