        Why place RateLimitFilter before JwtGlobalFilter?

        Suppose an attacker sends:

        100000 Requests
        Current flow
        100000

        ↓

        JWT Parsing

        ↓

        JWT Signature Verification

        ↓

        Claims Extraction

        ↓

        Routing

        The gateway spends CPU on every request before rejecting anything.

        New flow
        100000

        ↓

        RateLimitFilter

        ↓

        Allowed?

        ↓

        NO

        ↓

        429

        Only requests that pass the rate limit continue to JWT validation.

        This protects the gateway itself from excessive work.